    "recap_headline": "University of Delaware Athletics",
    "recap_text": "NEWARK, Del. -\nThe University of Delaware baseball program had its best team performance of the year, as the Fightin' Blue Hens defeated St. Joe's 18-0 in seven innings on Wednesday at Bob Hannah Stadium.\nWith the win, the Blue Hens overall record is now 9-12.\nHEN HIGHLIGHTS\nEvan Bouldin\nand\nAnthony DeCesare\nled the way for the Blue Hens offensively. Both of the batters went 3-for-3. Bouldin had a home run and five RBIs, DeCesare had three RBIs.\nUD's offense scored at least two run in six of the seven innings today.\nThe Blue Hens pitching staff of\nChase Deibler\n,\nNick Bilotto\n,\nBen Moyzan\nand\nEthan Shaub\npitched seven shutout innings, and allowed just one hit. Deibler was credited with the win, and is now 2-1.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nBouldin kicked off the game with a two-run home run in the bottom of the first, and scored\nJeremy Wolf\n.\nSal Mineo\ndrove in two runs in the second inning off a single, along with a\nVincent Davis\nwalk with the bases loaded, and scored Mineo.\nBoth Bouldin and Mineo drove in two runs each off singles in the third inning.\nDeCesare kept the Blue Hens offense humming in the fourth inning with a two run double to extend their lead to 10-0.\nThe Blue Hens scored eight runs in the sixth inning. The rally started with\nLuke Lambert\nreaching first off an error, and scored\nMatthew Minckler\n, and finished with a DeCesare RBI double to left field.\nGAME NOTES\nThe 18 runs is the most the Blue Hens offense has scored this season.\nThe one hit allowed is tied for the lowest under head coach\nGreg Mamula\n.\u00a0The last time the UD pitching staff allowed one hit was back on May 19, 2023 against Hofstra.\nUP NEXT\nDelaware will host Dallas Baptist from March 20-22 for a Conference USA matchup. It is the Blue Hens first home series as a member of CUSA.\nTICKETS\nSeason and individual tickets are available for all of Delaware's 2026 home games.\nClick here\nto secure your seats for the next game.\nFOLLOW ON SOCIAL\nFor the latest on Delaware baseball, follow the Blue Hens on\nX\n,\nInstagram\n, and like on\nFacebook\n."
